<br>
Gro. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uvelgair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Velgair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/24/02 11:05:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hahaha..</span><hr size=1> I had an instance where the group I was in killed the princess.  There were 2 skalds in the group including myself.  The other skald was 2 levels higher than I was.  We dropped the princess and she dropped some skald chain gloves.  The was given to me by whomever got it in the group.  The higher level skald cried and whined saying it wasn't fair.   So the group gave in and flamed me to give the gloves to him.  So I did, no big deal.  He gave me his old gloves, which were the same EXACT gloves but were less than half durability.  I became angry and suggested we roll for the new pair.  No dice.  The guy said HELL NO &quot;I am 2 levels higher than you&quot;  hehehe.  Oh well..funny now that I look back on it.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kilgour>Kilgour</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/24/02 12:15:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Piety?</span><hr size=1> I have heard (but not tested) that piety affects skald power, and charisma affects spell effects.<br>
<br>
Now, while not having tested this at all, I am certain it can be tested by any of our number crunchers.  Simple tests like # mezzes per power bar or slows, DDs etc, could show whether any of the Skald spells are affected by piety. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=313.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=313.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=313.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.threadControl?topicID=313.topic><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/closethread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=313.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=313.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub36.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="teamskaldfrm1">General Discussion<option value="teamskaldfrm6">Bug Forum<option value="teamskaldfrm5">Test Pla